<chapter xml:id="ch_circ-res" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Circuits: Resistors</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn about resistors in circuits.</p>
	
	<p><alert>Learning Outcomes</alert></p>
  
	<p>
		After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:
		<ol>
			<li>Determine the amount of current flowing through a circuit with one or more resistors and a single battery, both quantitatively and qualitatively.</li>
			<li>Determine the amount of current flowing through a circuit with one or more resistors and more than one battery, both quantitatively and qualitatively.</li>
			<li>Determine the equivalent resistance of a circuit.</li>
			<li>Determine the power and/or energy used by a resistor.</li>
		</ol>
	</p>

	</introduction>

